programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 1
programme.desc: Lizzy MacGill is a horse trainer's young daughter who elopes with Garth Armstrong, a privileged man.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Thoroughbreds - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark try to help Lizzie. The new bride has cancer and she is pregnant.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song for Jason - Part 1
programme.desc: Mark and Jonathan become counselors at a camp for children with cancer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: A Song for Jason - Part 2
programme.desc: Jonathan and Mark are helping patients at Camp Good Times in different ways. But a father still refuses to deal with his son's illness.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Bless the Boys in Blue
programme.desc: Jonathan relinquishes his angelic powers for awhile and realizes the dangers that Mark has faced being a police officer.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: Cindy
programme.desc: An aspiring actress wants to be accepted for who she really is, not in the image her well-meaning dad tries to transform her into.

programme.title: Highway to Heaven: The Devil and Jonathan Smith
programme.desc: Mark has been tricked into selling his soul in order to save a little girl's life. But the Devil has another agenda: acquiring Jonathan's soul.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Richard Power
programme.desc: Serial socialiser and budding nightclub entrepreneur Richard Power knows he looks old for his age. But even when a poll of 100 people confirm his thoughts he has difficulty accepting it's because he's drinking 35 pints a week and 40 cigarettes a day.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Shirley Maddison
programme.desc: Shirley's lack of self confidence stems from her poor self image. She thinks she looks old. She's not the only one. A public poll guessed her age at 52. The time for serious intervention has arrived from Nicky Hambleton-Jones.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Laura Hammond
programme.desc: 34 year old Laura Hammond has a body to die for. Her stomach is flat; her slim legs go all the way up to her chin and she's got the sassy ass of a super model. According to a poll of 100 Mancunians, this young woman looks like a 48 year old!

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Finding Her Hidden Value
programme.desc: Tracy is a real estate appraiser who can't seem to find the value in her looks. She works in a man's world where her clothes are usually more butch than beautiful. With a new job starting soon, Tracy needs to re-vamp her look fast.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Officer Hottie
programme.desc: Rosario is Mr. Mom by day and a New York City police officer by night. He spends his life outdoors which has done a number on his skin while his massive dental issues have done a number on his wallet. We're going to try to make him look 10 Years Younger.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Different Strokes
programme.desc: Zuri is a hard working single mother of two with no time or energy for herself. In a relationship with a man her own age who looks younger, she is embarrassed to be mistaken for his mother. The Glam Squad does their magic to roll back the years.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Rockin' Mom
programme.desc: Suddenly, Eva is a new wife and mother. This change in lifestyle has found her lazy and abandoning her once trendy and hip sense of style. Experts are waiting in the wings to refresh this weary mother.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: A Very Tall Order
programme.desc: This part-time model traded in her big city lifestyle for a family in the suburbs. Mylene's appearance has taken a backseat to her kids and full-time job. She needs a team of experts to update her look and give her a quick shot of confidence.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Hippie To Happening
programme.desc: Albert loves traveling and trying new things, except when it comes to his appearance. Albert's bad divorce has left him feeling self-conscious about the lines on his face and his graying, thinning hair.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger UK: Bernie Sharp "One Year On"
programme.desc: Last year, 45 year old prison worker Bernie Sharp was looking 51 – or so said one hundred straight-talking strangers on a street in Manchester. One year on, we retrace the rollercoaster journey to a brand new Bernie.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Ground Down Mom
programme.desc: Dawn designs swimming pools and home-schools her daughter, but this can-do mom can't take time for herself. Cosmetic dentistry and high-tech dermatology remove the visible effects of stress, and the Glam Squad brings her inner beauty to the surface.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: One Busy Momma
programme.desc: Yesenia is a busy hard working wife, mother of twin teenagers and a toddler, who is constantly on the go and has no time for herself. It's our mission to give her the time and attention she deserves and help her feel more vibrant again.

programme.title: 10 Years Younger USA: Back in the Limelight
programme.desc: As Nicole began to age, she felt she didn't look the part of a rock singer anymore and she left the stage for good, leaving behind her life's dream. The Glam Squad and our team of doctors will work hard to get Nicole back on stage again.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 9
programme.desc: The family are making arrangements to leave Leopard's Den, all except Du Plessis who is steadfastly refusing to accept that he has lost his home. He won't use his share of the money from the sale of the land to buy somewhere else.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 10
programme.desc: The family have been squatting at Leopard's Den as they prepare to make their last stand to prevent the bulldozers from destroying their home. Du Plessis and Fatani bring elephants and a giraffe to dissuade the construction crew from moving in.

programme.title: Wild At Heart
programme.desc: After the devastating loss of Leopard's Den, the family are split across continents. Caroline, Liv and a heavily pregnant Alice are in the UK, while Danny and Du Plessis have remained in South Africa.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 2
programme.desc: Danny returns to South Africa with Caroline, Liv and Charlotte. They are all excited to be back and are looking forward to seeing their new home, Clearwater Farm.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 3
programme.desc: Danny has been preparing his pitch for an Endangered Species Project. JLW, a pharmaceutical company, are looking to fund an environmental project and the family hope that this grant money will enable them to buy Leopard's Den and Mara.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 4
programme.desc: Danny and Ed release two cheetah brothers together, a symbol of their new partnership, but not all of the family are happy about this new start. Caroline is still furious at what she sees as Danny's betrayal of Du Plessis.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 5
programme.desc: The family are still estranged following Caroline's decision to move back to the decrepit Clearwater house with Du Plessis. Rosie is determined to reunite everyone, and plans a civilised dinner as a step towards reconciliation.

programme.title: Wild At Heart: Episode 6
programme.desc: Danny is in prison, accused of murdering Peeters, but Du Plessis is determined to prove his friend's innocence by any means he can. Du Plessis' first attempt backfires disastrously when he harangues a police officer and ends up in a cell next to Danny.

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 26
programme.desc: Film buff Paul and footy mad Scott go head to head as their partners down tools and go on strike for four days. As they juggle the housework and the kids, which dad will cope best?

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 27
programme.desc: Engineer Ayo and cabbie Darren go head to head as their partners down tools and go on strike for four days. As they juggle the housework and the kids, which dad will cope best with the challenges?

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 28
programme.desc: Wrestler Chris and bathroom fitter Stuart go head to head as their partners down tools and go on strike for four days. As they juggle the housework and the kids, which dad will cope best?

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 29
programme.desc: Golf addict Richard and sports car fanatic Blaine go head to head as their partners down tools and go on strike for four days. As they juggle the housework and the kids, which dad will cope best?

programme.title: I Want My Mummy!: Episode 30
programme.desc: Money man Eric and builder Steve go head to head as their partners down tools and go on strike for four days. As they juggle the housework and the kids, which dad will cope best with the challenges?

programme.title: The Boy Who Can't Forget
programme.desc: Twenty-year-old British student Aurelien is one of just a handful of people in the world who are baffling scientists with their ability to recall an incredible amount of their lives. He is the first Briton to go public with this extraordinary talent.

programme.title: Big Families: Can't Stop, Won't Stop
programme.desc: We meet three families who are either expecting or planning a baby at the same time as seeing their older children, grow up, move out and start their own families.

programme.title: Big Families: Sibling Rivalry
programme.desc: Our first family have 10 children between the ages of a few months and their early teens. With all of the children so close in age, all of the kids are still at a stage where they desperately need their parents love and attention.

programme.title: Big Families: Price and Prejudice
programme.desc: Our first family are determined not to take government handouts. Dad works, mum stays at home and does the odd job and they budget to stay afloat. In their opinion, it was their choice to have 12 children so it's their responsibility to look after them.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Salto Mortale
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept face a new mission: performing a front-flip through the air with a stuntman on board of an estate wagon. It's a new task for coordinator and adrenaline junkie Christoph Domi Domanski.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Remote Control
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept try out another new stunt: Stuntman Tobi, aka Heidi, operates an Artega GT at full speed with a remote control. This is, however, just a warm-up before the big stunt, in which he drives a car up a steep ramp.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Graduate
programme.desc: This is what it looks like when the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept perform a long jump: a vehicle jumps at full speed over four cars, which explode one after the other. It’s a matter of precision and timing.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Very First Time
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from the Action Concept are shooting a car rollover. But stunt coordinator Carl wants to go the whole hog. His motto: if you’re going to do something at all, you might as well do it properly!

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Highfall
programme.desc: While most people never had a car crash, they know spectacular car crashes with huge explosions from movies. But these scenes are much more sensational than in real life, because cars hardly ever explode.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Behind the Scenes
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are tough professionals. They jump from houses and make cars fly or explode. On this episode, reporter Dean Malay takes a look behind the scenes of the stunt company.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Bike stunts
programme.desc: This time the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept deal with motorbike stunts: high jumps, risky drops and dangerous crashes. As usual, stunt coordinator Domi requires his motorbike specialists Daniel and Marcel to be in top form.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Ambulance
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are always looking for new spectacular stunts and are not running out of options. Stunt coordinator Domi’s latest idea involves an old ambulance.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The Matrix
programme.desc: Martial arts specialist Ramazan creates a choreography for a fight. It involves four stuntmen who need to disguise as secret agents and bash on him. Will Ramazan be able to free himself from this uncomfortable position?

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Multiple Collision
programme.desc: Fog, darkness and a pileup involving multiple cars: It's a scene that you can often see on highways and it's a scene that the Stunt Heroes from Action Concept want to recreate as part of a stunt with burning people.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: The White Army
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept leave their headquarters behind and travel to a ski resort. Between the trees of a nearby forest they simulate the attack of an army of white-dressed soldiers.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Alarm in the Ski Resort
programme.desc: The Stunt Heroes from Action Concept are still at their ski resort and party hard. This time they prepared a spectacular stunt involving a station wagon. It is thrown 50 meters into the air with a cannon.

programme.title: Stunt Heroes: Body Stunt Highlights
programme.desc: Today it's Action Concepts most popular and most spectacular body stunts: Jumping from rooftops, falling of a driving car, tumbling down stairs. Despite inevitable wounds, the legendary stunt crew enjoys the job.

programme.title: Supercars: 40 Years of BMW M
programme.desc: Supercars celebrates the unbelievable success of the BMW M Ltd. It all began in 1972 with the M1, one of the style icons of the supercars.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Lost Generation
programme.desc: A CVI malfunctions and kills a soon-to-be father. The investigation leads Liam and Renee to a fertility clinic. Renee finds out she is infertile and suspects that Taelon technology is affecting worldwide fertility.

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: The Summit

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Trapped by Time

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Atonement

programme.title: Earth: Final Conflict: Blood Ties
programme.desc: Strange assaults and several deaths may be related to a Doors/Taelon joint venture where Taelon core energy was used to heal people. It appears that the energy is being sucked back out of the patients.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 5
programme.desc: A young man has flipped his quad bike and can't move his neck. Later that night, the crew is called to a suburban house because a DIY homebuilder has fallen through the roof in his house – and there's a bone sticking out through his jeans.

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 6
programme.desc: De Anna and her husband were celebrating their 50th wedding anniversary on board a luxury liner. The ship's doctor radios for help. But the liner is a long way out at sea. Can the rescue crew get to De Anna in time?

programme.title: Air Rescue: Episode 1
programme.desc: 14 year-old motor-cross rider, Kacee gets the death wobbles and cartwheels over the top of his handle bars and hits the ground head first. He's now struggling to breath and is barely able to talk. Team Air Rescue needs to get Kacee to the hospital fast.

programme.title: Supercars: 40 Years of BMW M

programme.title: Supercars: James Bond Special

programme.title: Supercars: Asian Bestsellers

programme.title: Supercars: Lamborghini
programme.desc: On this episode of Supercars, men's inner strength comes alive. Sant Agata Bolognese, the home of Lamborghini, is the ideal place to take the Gallardo models out for a spin. Plus: the fastest city tour in the world.

programme.title: Supercars: Best of 2012

programme.title: Supercars: Porsche to the Max!

programme.title: Supercars: Luxury SUVs

programme.title: Supercars: Pagani Story
programme.desc: For petrolheads the name Pagani is a synonym of the roaring sound of thunder. This is due to the 12-cylinder high-performance engine used by the Italian sports car manufacturer to make the ground shake.

programme.title: Supercars: Hot Supercars

programme.title: Supercars: German Supercars

programme.title: Supercars: Motor Show Geneva
programme.desc: There are details which set supercars apart from normal cars and these details are essential. Supercars are the biggest, loudest and most expensive cars on the highway; they're four-wheeled works of art.

programme.title: Supercars: V8 Power

programme.title: Supercars: British Power

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Rains Down

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Red Highway
programme.desc: The elderly owners of a local grocery are attacked and left for dead. Working with a vague witness description, Lt. Joe Kenda leads a state-wide manhunt to catch a pair of cold-blooded killers.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Fate Worst Than Death
programme.desc: At the bottom of a steep ravine, joggers discover a body mutilated beyond recognition. To catch a ruthless maniac, Lt. Joe Kenda must first solve the puzzle of the victim’s identity.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter
programme.desc: When police find 24-year-old Patrick Ray with a gunshot to the temple, the scene has all the telltale signs of suicide. But Lt. Joe Kenda's instinct says otherwise.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Sisters
programme.desc: The bullet-ridden bodies of two sisters are found in a suburban house that’s littered with mysterious clues. Joe Kenda learns that the two unassuming young mothers shared an explosive secret.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Death Grip
programme.desc: When a speeding truck crashes into a residential building, officers find the lifeless body of Michael Faast behind the wheel. But he didn’t die in the wreck – he was shot point-blank in the temple.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Blood Innocence
programme.desc: War hero Carl Taylor is beaten to death in the back of an empty semi truck, for no apparent reason. Lt Joe Kenda notices an unusual pattern in the victim’s head wounds.

programme.title: Homicide Hunter: Eyes Wide Shut
programme.desc: A park ranger discovers the corpse of amateur boxer Corey Edge floating in a shallow creek. Kenda learns the victim had ties to the criminal underworld, and investigates a rogue’s gallery of hustlers.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar's Worst Bite
programme.desc: Holly, a Labrador puppy, displays severe food aggression; a women's shelter will take a needy woman and her pit bull, Tucker, but Cesar must help the dog become less protective first.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Cesar Conquers London
programme.desc: There's anarchy in the UK as Cesar faces a challenge from a rowdy Jack Russell, two culture-shocked pooches and an unruly Patterdale terrier mix.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Sadie and Calder
programme.desc: Allen and Erin Carrasco ‘s Basset Hound Sadie whines and moans whenever Allen is around. Blue Heeler mix Calder is a great dog by day, but bedtime rituals unleash unwelcome night terrors.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Lives Changed
programme.desc: In this special episode, Cesar revisits some of the incredible Dog Whisperer stories of the past four years and shares his reactions to the changes in the lives of these special packs.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Kiko, Tootsie & Ginger, and Binkey
programme.desc: A bullying miniature pinscher moves to Camp Pendleton. A Chihuahua mix. Writer, actor and director Mike White’s French bulldogs are out of control.

programme.title: The Dog Whisperer: Duke & Lulu, and Sparky
programme.desc: Cesar heads to the dog park to help some frustrated dog lovers. A therapeutic terrier helps AJ control her panic attacks but tends to attack other dogs.
